==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ideation
<hw>I`de*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The faculty or
capacity of the mind for forming ideas; the exercise of this capacity;
the act of the mind by which objects of sense are apprehended and
retained as objects of thought.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The whole mass of residua which have been accumulated . . . all
enter now into the process of <qex>ideation</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J. D.
Morell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ideational</ent>⟦br⟧
